@jerryshao, the intent is to delegate to the correct catalog for each table and not, for example, to call the Iceberg catalog to delete a Hive table.

That's why `loadTable` uses a try/catch: Hive was updated to throw `NotIcebergException` (extends `NoSuchTableException`) if a table is not Iceberg. So Iceberg will throw an exception and the table will be loaded from Hive instead.

I've updated a couple of methods in the new catalog (rename and alter) as well as the Hive catalog to ensure that's the behavior that is implemented.
